Time Series SQL Analytics
Project Overview

This project focuses on time series analysis using MySQL and realistic electricity market price data.

The objective is to demonstrate SQL techniques commonly used in reporting, business intelligence, and energy market analytics, including:

Daily, weekly, and monthly reporting
Rolling averages
Trend analysis
Volatility measurement
Peak vs Off-Peak analysis
Window functions
Market anomaly detection

The project simulates the type of reporting and analytical tasks typically performed by Energy Market Analysts, BI Analysts, and Data Analysts.

Business Scenario

An electricity market analysis team monitors hourly market prices and prepares recurring reports for management.

The reporting process requires:

Daily market summaries
Weekly trend monitoring
Monthly performance reporting
Identification of unusual market behavior
Tracking of long-term price trends

The goal is to transform raw hourly market prices into actionable business insights using SQL.

Dataset

The analysis uses hourly electricity market price data stored in MySQL.

Dataset characteristics:

8,760 hourly observations
Full calendar year coverage
Peak and Off-Peak classification
Realistic seasonal behavior
Price spikes and negative price events

Main table used:

market_prices
Column	Description
price_id	Unique record identifier
market_id	Market identifier
price_date	Observation date
price_timestamp	Observation timestamp
settlement_price	Electricity market price (€/MWh)
hour	Hour of day
peak_type	Peak / Off-Peak classification
