Business Questions Answered
Daily Reporting
What was the average electricity price each day?

Used to monitor daily market performance.

Which days experienced the highest volatility?

Used to identify unstable market conditions.

How different were Peak and Off-Peak prices?

Used to evaluate demand-driven pricing behavior.

Weekly Reporting
Which weeks had the highest average prices?

Used to identify sustained high-price periods.

How did prices change week-over-week?

Used to monitor market trends.

Monthly Reporting
Which month was the most expensive?

Used for seasonal analysis.

Which month showed the highest volatility?

Used to evaluate market uncertainty.

Advanced Time Series Analytics
Rolling 7-Day Average

Used to smooth short-term market fluctuations and identify trends.

Rolling 30-Day Average

Used to evaluate longer-term market behavior.

Running Maximum

Tracks the highest average market price observed up to each point in time.

Running Minimum

Tracks the lowest average market price observed up to each point in time.

Market Monitoring
Price Spike Detection

Market prices were categorized into:

Normal
High
Extreme

Used to identify unusual market events.

Price Distribution Analysis

Market observations were grouped into price bands to understand market behavior and frequency of price events.

Volatility Analysis

Daily and monthly volatility were calculated using:

STDDEV(settlement_price)

Volatility is commonly used in energy markets to measure price uncertainty and market risk.

SQL Objects Created
Views

Created reusable reporting layers:

vw_daily_market_summary
vw_monthly_market_summary
vw_trader_performance
Stored Procedures

Created reusable reporting procedures:

sp_daily_market_summary()
sp_monthly_market_summary()
